Governor Ahmadu Umaru Fintri of Adamawa State has emerged winner of the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) governorship primaries in the state. Fintri polled 663 of the 668 votes, with five of the votes declared void, Channels Tv reports. The Adamawa Governor and his Deputy, Serth Crowder, were sworn in for their first term on May 29 2019. Chairman of the committee, Gibson Kataps, a former Secretary to the Taraba State Government (SSG) who announced the votes, declared Ahmadu Fintiri as the duly elected PDP governorship candidate for the 2023 general election. Responding, Fintiri thanked the delegates for their ‘massive support’ and promised that he would consolidate on his achievements as governor so far and launch stomach infrastructure projects if he returns as governor after the 2023 general election.